      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h3>Are digital waivers legally binding?</h3>
      <p>Yes. E-signatures are legally binding under the ESIGN Act (US), UETA, and eIDAS (EU), provided they include proper timestamping, IP logging, and consumer consent to electronic signatures.</p>

      <h3>How long should I keep signed waivers?</h3>
      <p>Retention requirements vary by state. Most states require 3-7 years. Check your local health department regulations. Cloud storage makes retention easy — set it and forget it.</p>

      <h3>Can clients fill out waivers before arriving?</h3>
      <p>Yes. The best practice is to send the waiver link automatically when the booking is confirmed. Client fills it out on their phone at home — they arrive ready to tattoo.</p>

      <h3>What if a client doesn't have a smartphone?</h3>
      <p>Have a tablet at the front desk for clients without smartphones. Place it on a stand with hand sanitizer nearby. Most digital waiver platforms work on any device with a browser.</p>

